The minister of Humanitarian Affairs, Disaster Management and Social Development, Hajia Sadiya Umar Farouq, has recounted achievements of the ministry since its creation and applauded President Muhammadu Buhari for touching lives through the ministry. She said this during the celebration of the ministry’s first anniversary, yesterday, in Abuja, adding President Muhammadu Buhari, in his wisdom deemed it fit to create a ministry that would institutionalize all governments efforts towards social inclusion and response to disasters and humanitarian crisis while providing the much-needed coordination of humanitarian interventions. Farouq said the ministry is mandated to develop humanitarian policies and provide effective coordination of national and international humanitarian interventions; while ensuring strategic disaster mitigation, preparedness and response, adding the ministry is also charged with the responsibility of managing the formulation and implementation of fair focused social inclusion and protection programmes in Nigeria. “So far, for the one year we have been in existence, I would say it has been an eventful, challenging and rewarding journey.” Challenging in the sense that the ministry is saddled with the responsibility of overseeing responsibilities that were hitherto domiciled in other MDAs, and also providing the much-needed coordination of humanitarian interventions in Nigeria. It is rewarding in the sense that when we visit the field and see beneficiaries whose lives are being changed by the FG humanitarian interventions, it leaves us with a sense of fulfilment that we are doing something worthwhile for humanity,” she stated.